# Development Blocks and SDK Auto-Seeking

This rule maps **task types** to the correct `.cursor/llm/docs/` files, skills, and existing building blocks. Use it so the agent automatically seeks the right SDKs and prefers registry and project components over new one-off code.

## Blocks-First Policy

- **Prefer registry and existing project components** over writing new code from scratch.
- **Check** the AI SDK Elements registry, shadcn components, and existing `apps/studio/components/` (or equivalent) before adding a new UI component or page.
- **Only add** new components or new SDK usage when no existing block fits; then document or add to the project's component/index as appropriate.

## Pre-Implement Checklist (New Page, Route, Component, or API)

Before implementing a **new** page, route, component, or API endpoint:

1. **List applicable SDK/LLM docs** from `.cursor/llm/docs/` (see `.cursor/llm/llm.txt` for the index) for the task type below.
2. **List applicable skills** from `.cursor/skills/` and `docs/planning/INSTALLED_SKILLS.md`.
3. **Check registry and existing components**: AI Elements registry (https://elements.ai-sdk.dev/api/registry/all.json), shadcn UI, and existing project components (e.g. `apps/studio/components/`) for something reusable.
4. **Then implement** using those blocks and patterns.

Do not skip this checklist for net-new surface area (new page, new route, new UI component, new API route).

## Task-Type to Resource Mapping

Use this table to choose which LLM docs and skills to read for each kind of work. Paths under **Globs** indicate when this rule is auto-applied; for other paths, still apply the mapping when the task matches.

### New page or route (Studio frontend)

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/nextjs-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/nextjs-react-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/elements-ai-sdk.txt` |
| **Skills** | nextjs-react-typescript, implement-design, frontend-design (or equivalent in `.cursor/skills/`) |
| **Blocks to check first** | AI SDK Elements registry, shadcn UI, `apps/studio/components/`, existing pages with similar layout in `apps/studio/app/` |

When editing under **`apps/studio/**`**: Consult elements-ai-sdk, theme/design system, and existing Studio components; prefer registry and project components.

### New API or backend route

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/fastapi-llm.txt`; OpenAPI/spec if present |
| **Skills** | fastapi, fastapi-templates, supabase-postgres-best-practices (if DB involved) |
| **Blocks to check first** | Existing routes in the same service, shared middleware, API patterns in `services/` or `apps/*-api/` |

When editing under **`services/**` or **`apps/*-api/**`**: Consult fastapi-llm, OpenAPI/spec, and FastAPI skills.

### New chat/agent UI (component or screen)

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/elements-ai-sdk.txt`; `.cursor/llm/docs/anthropic-openai-llm.txt` or gemini/langchain if wiring providers |
| **Skills** | ai-sdk (`.cursor/skills/ai-sdk`), nextjs-react-typescript |
| **Blocks to check first** | AI SDK Elements registry (Conversation, Message, PromptInput, Agent, Tool, etc.); do not build custom chat UI before checking the registry |

Use AI SDK Elements registry and existing chat/agent components before introducing custom chat UI.

### New contract or deploy flow

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/thirdweb-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/hardhat-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/hardhat-foundry-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/erc-4337-llm.txt` (and other ERC-* / x402 docs as relevant) |
| **Skills** | solidity-development, smart-contract-security, solidity-security |
| **Blocks to check first** | Existing contract templates, deploy scripts, chain adapters in the repo |

### New UI component (any app)

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/elements-ai-sdk.txt` (if AI-related), `.cursor/llm/docs/nextjs-react-llm.txt` |
| **Skills** | nextjs-react-typescript, implement-design, ui-components (if using shadcn/Radix) |
| **Blocks to check first** | AI Elements registry, shadcn, `apps/studio/components/` (or the app’s component folder) |

When editing under **`**/components/**`**: Check AI Elements registry and project design system first; prefer existing blocks.

### Orchestration / agent pipeline (backend)

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/langgraph-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/langchain-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/fastapi-llm.txt` |
| **Skills** | langgraph, langgraph-docs, langchain-architecture, fastapi |
| **Blocks to check first** | Existing orchestrator nodes, agent definitions, and route handlers |

### Data / persistence

| Resource | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **LLM docs** | `.cursor/llm/docs/supabase-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/redis-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/pinecone-llm.txt`, `.cursor/llm/docs/acontext-llm.txt` (as applicable) |
| **Skills** | supabase-postgres-best-practices, database-schema-designer |
| **Blocks to check first** | Existing schemas, migrations, and service clients in the repo |

## Globs and Auto-Apply

This rule is applied automatically when editing files under:

- **`apps/studio/**`** — Studio frontend: use elements-ai-sdk, theme, registry, and existing Studio components.
- **`services/**`** — Backend services: use fastapi-llm, OpenAPI, and FastAPI skills.
- **`apps/*-api/**`** — API apps: same as backend.
- **`**/components/**`** — Any UI components: check AI Elements registry and project design system first.

For other paths, still follow the task-type mapping and blocks-first policy when the task is a new page, route, component, or API.

